                <h2>Ways you can take care of your dog companion!</h2>
                <ul class="tips-list">
                    <li><strong>Provide a Balanced Diet:</strong> Feed your dog high-quality food suitable for their breed and age.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ensure Fresh Water Availability:</strong> Keep clean water accessible at all times.</li>
                    <li><strong>Regular Exercise:</strong> Take your dog for daily walks and playtime to maintain their health.</li>
                    <li><strong>Routine Veterinary Check-ups:</strong> Schedule regular vet visits for vaccinations and health assessments.</li>
                    <li><strong>Grooming and Hygiene:</strong> Bathe your dog as needed and brush their coat to prevent matting.</li>
                    <li><strong>Dental Care:</strong> Brush your dog's teeth regularly to avoid dental issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Training and Socialization:</strong> Train your dog and expose them to different environments to build good behavior.</li>
                    <li><strong>Safe Living Environment:</strong> Ensure your home is dog-proofed to prevent accidents.</li>
                    <li><strong>Proper Identification:</strong> Use ID tags or microchips to ensure your dog can be found if lost.</li>
                    <li><strong>Show Love and Attention:</strong> Spend quality time with your dog to strengthen your bond.</li>
                </ul>
